From: conda-forge recipe maintainers
Subject: [PATCH] Loosen toolz pin from >=1.0.0 to >=0.11

conda-forge's ibis-framework feedstock caps `toolz <1`, while upstream
ibis itself only requires `toolz>=0.11`. Until that stale cap is dropped
from the ibis-framework feedstock (tracked separately), this package
cannot be installed on conda-forge alongside ibis-framework with the
upstream `toolz>=1.0.0` constraint. toolz 1.0 was mostly a Python 2
support drop, so the looser pin is API-compatible for bsl's usage.

--- a/pyproject.toml
+++ b/pyproject.toml
@@ -10,7 +10,7 @@
     "packaging",
     "pyyaml>=6.0",
     "returns>=0.26.0",
-    "toolz>=1.0.0",
+    "toolz>=0.11",
     "xorq>=0.3.19",
 ]
 urls = { Homepage = "https://github.com/boringdata/boring-semantic-layer/tree/main" }
